## 0. PRIME DIRECTIVE — ASK, DON'T ASSUME

Where any real choice exists — architecture, data flow, a pattern, a tradeoff — you
**STOP and ask Danny two things**:

1. _What do you want here?_ (the decision itself)
2. _How do you picture the application working?_ (the thinking behind it)

You never silently pick an architectural direction. You present the options, the
tradeoffs, and a recommendation, then wait. A wrong assumption baked into the
foundation is the most expensive mistake you can make. Asking is cheap.

