## 3. AUDIT DIMENSIONS (what you check, every pass)

For each dimension you produce a verdict: **PASS / FAIL**, with file, line, and fix.

### 3.1 Modularity

```
// Each component does ONE thing and is reusable
```

- Components have a single responsibility; no "god components"
- Shared UI (cards, drawers, chart wrappers) lives in `components/ui` or
  `components/charts`, not copy-pasted per page
- Page components compose small parts; they don't inline 400 lines of chart logic

### 3.2 Consistency

```
// Same problem solved the same way everywhere
```

- Naming is uniform (files, props, handlers, state)
- **Every** network call uses `api.get()/api.post()` from `src/lib/api.js` — never
  raw `fetch` or a bare axios instance (this is how tenant scoping is guaranteed)
- Internal references use Danny's own UUID `id`, never ShiftManager's `external_id`
- Filter / drill-down / KPI patterns follow the established shape

### 3.3 Duplication

```
// No copy-paste — extract shared logic into helpers or components
```

- Repeated chart-data shaping belongs in `lib/chartHelpers.js`
- Repeated formatting (dates, status badges) is extracted, not re-declared per file
- Flag any block that appears in 2+ places with a single-source-of-truth fix

### 3.4 File-size cap

```
// 1000 lines is the hard ceiling — over it means split it
```

- Any file over the cap is a **finding**, with a concrete split proposal
- Prefer splitting by responsibility, not by arbitrary line count

### 3.5 Security (frontend-specific — high priority)

```
// The client is untrusted — treat it that way
```

- **No secrets in client code** (API keys, tokens, internal URLs) — BLOCKER if found
- XSS surface: no unsanitised `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`; user/content data escaped
- Auth handled via httpOnly cookies; tokens never written to `localStorage`/JS-readable
  storage (note: browser storage also breaks in some sandboxes — flag both issues)
- No tenant data leakage: the client never trusts a tenant id from anywhere but the
  authenticated session; it cannot request another tenant's data by changing a value
- No sensitive fields rendered that the backend policy marks hidden

### 3.6 Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA)

```
// Usable by everyone — contrast, focus, labels, keyboard
```

- Interactive elements are keyboard reachable and labelled
- Colour is never the only signal; contrast meets AA
- Drawers/modals trap focus and restore it on close

### 3.7 Legibility for external reviewers (the cost lever)

```
// Every code block carries a short English comment saying what it does
```

- **This is mandatory and you enforce it AND follow it.** Every meaningful block of
  code — a function, an effect, a handler, a data transform — has a one-line English
  comment above it explaining what that block does. Not why-essays; what-it-does.
- The goal is explicit: an external developer should grasp any block in seconds, so
  onboarding costs hours instead of days.
- Files read top-to-bottom like a narrated story.

