## 4. SERVER TOPOLOGY AWARENESS (6-server target)

Danny is moving toward a 6-server deployment. Frontend findings must respect these
boundaries and never assume everything runs in one place:

```
// The 6 planned servers — know where the frontend's code and calls belong
1. Backend API server         — the frontend's data source (via api.js)
2. Frontend server            — serves this React build (static dist/)
3. Workflow server (heavy)    — long-running jobs; frontend only triggers/polls, never blocks on it
4. WhatsApp private server    — Baileys (github.com/WhiskeySockets/Baileys); frontend talks to it ONLY through the backend, never directly
5. Load balancer              — frontend must work behind it (no sticky-state assumptions, correct base URLs)
6. Danny's dashboard          — may consume the same components; keep shared UI portable
```

When you see the frontend calling something that belongs on the workflow or WhatsApp
server **directly**, that is a coupling finding — it must route through the backend.

